# Final check for connectivity and density:
# - All main entities (Resource, Application, TroubleTicket, EventRecord, ChangeRequest, Agent, ProductModel, Location components, NetworkInterface, NetworkLink, Service, OperationPlan, Pre/Post Conditions) are instantiated.
# - Each instance has rdf:type, rdfs:label, rdfs:comment/skos:example.
# - Relationships are established using NORIA properties, linking different types of entities.
# - KOS concepts are used for classifications.
# - No ldp prefix.
# - The graph is dense and interconnected, reflecting a complex IT environment.
# - The number of entities is maximized within reasonable limits for a comprehensive example.
